Chelsea manager, Frank Lampard, has heaped praises on Striker, Tammy Abraham ahead of his side’s Premier League clash with Norwich City on Saturday. Chelsea head to the game after playing a 1-1 with Leicester City in their last Premier League fixture. Speaking at his pre-match press conference on Friday, Lampard hailed Abraham’s attitude in the first few weeks of the new season. ”We work hard on the training pitch for that. What I have got is great attitudes in the three strikers and the other players,” Lampard said. ”Tammy’s goes in off the post at United it is a different story. It’s about belief.” Abraham is competing with Olivier Giroud and Michy Batshuayi for a starting shirt against Norwich. The kick-off time for the match is 12:30pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.